IsASCIICapable.description: Custom Keyboard: A Boolean value that specifies whether a custom keyboard supports the UIKeyboardTypeASCIICapable keyboard type trait. See IsASCIICapable for details.

NSExtension.description: General: A dictionary of keys and values that describe an app extension. See NSExtension for details.

NSExtensionActionWantsFullScreenPresenta.description: Action: A Boolean value that specifies whether the Action extension should be presented in full screen. See NSExtensionActionWantsFullScreenPresentation for details.

NSExtensionActivationDictionaryVersion.description: Share, Action: An integer that specifies the activation dictionary version to employ. See NSExtensionActivationDictionaryVersion for details.

NSExtensionActivationRule.description: Share, Action: A dictionary that specifies the semantic data types that a Share or Action extension supports. See NSExtensionActivationRule for details.

NSExtensionActivationUsesStrictMatching.description: Share, Action: See NSExtensionActivationUsesStrictMatching for details.

NSExtensionAttributes.description: General: A dictionary of keys and values that specify aspects of an app extension. See NSExtensionAttributes for details.

NSExtensionFileProviderDocumentGroup.description: Document Picker: A string that specifies the identifier of a shared container that can be accessed by a document picker and its associated file provider. See NSExtensionFileProviderDocumentGroup for details.

NSExtensionJavaScriptPreprocessingFile.description: Share, Action: A string that specifies the name of a JavaScript file supplied by a Share extension or an Action extension. See NSExtensionJavaScriptPreprocessingFile for details.

NSExtensionMainStoryboard.description: General: A string that specifies the name of the app extension’s main storyboard file, minus the .storyboard filename extension. See NSExtensionMainStoryboard for details.

NSExtensionOverridesHostUIAppearance.description: General: A Boolean value that specifies whether the app extension should ignore appearance updates made by the host app. See NSExtensionOverridesHostUIAppearance for details.

NSExtensionPointIdentifier.description: General: A string that specifies the extension point that supports an app extension, in reverse-DNS notation. See NSExtensionPointIdentifier for details.

NSExtensionPrincipalClass.description: General: A string that specifies the name of the custom class that implements an app extension’s primary view or functionality. See NSExtensionPrincipalClass for details.

NSExtensionServiceAllowsToolbarItem.description: Action: A Boolean value that specifies whether an Action extension can display a toolbar button in a window’s toolbar. See NSExtensionServiceAllowsToolbarItem for details.

NSExtensionServiceRoleType.description: Action: A string that specifies the type of task an Action extension can perform. See NSExtensionServiceRoleType for details.

NSExtensionServiceToolbarIconFile.description: Action: A string that species the icon file for an OS X Action extension’s toolbar button. See NSExtensionServiceToolbarIconFile for details.

NSExtensionServiceToolbarPaletteLabel.description: Action: A string that specifies the toolbar item title that gets displayed in the toolbar customization dialog for an Action extension. See NSExtensionServiceToolbarPaletteLabel for details.

PHSupportedMediaTypes.description: Photo Editing: An array that specifies the types of assets a Photo Editing extension can edit. See PHSupportedMediaTypes for details.

PrefersRightToLeft.description: Custom Keyboard: A Boolean value that specifies whether a custom keyboard is for a right-to-left language. See PrefersRightToLeft for details.

PrimaryLanguage.description: Custom Keyboard: A string conforming to BCP 47 - Tags for Identifying Languages, that specifies the primary language for custom keyboard. See PrimaryLanguage for details.

RequestsOpenAccess.description: Custom Keyboard: A Boolean value that specifies whether a custom keyboard wants to use a shared container and wants network access. See RequestsOpenAccess for details.

SFSafariContentScript.description: Safari: An array used to add content scripts to the extension. Each value in the array is a dictionary, providing the filename for a content script. See SFSafariContentScript for details.

SFSafariContextMenu.description: Safari: An array used to add items to Safari’s context menu. See SFSafariContextMenufor details.

SFSafariStyleSheet.description: Safari: An array used to add style sheets to the extension. Each value in the array is a dictionary, providing the filename for a content script. See SFSafariStyleSheet for details.

SFSafariToolbarItem.description: Safari: A dictionary used to add a toolbar item to Safari windows. See SFSafariToolbarItem for details.

SFSafariWebsiteAccess.description: Safari: An optional dictionary that specifies which webpages the Safari app extension can access, if any. See SFSafariWebsiteAccess for details.

UIDocumentPickerModes.description: Document Picker: An array that specifies the supported document picker modes. See UIDocumentPickerModes for details.

UIDocumentPickerSupportedFileTypes.description: Document Picker: An array that specifies the supported Uniform Type Identifiers (UTIs) for a document picker. See UIDocumentPickerSupportedFileTypes for details.

NSExtensionFileProviderActions.description: Defines custom actions for a File Provider extension. Your project must contain both a File Provider extension and a File Provider UI extension.
